==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Arrack
<hw>Ar"rack</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.
<ets>araq</ets> sweat, juice, spirituous liquor, fr. <ets>araqa</ets> to
sweat. Cf. <er>Rack</er> arrack.]</ety> <def>A name in the East Indies
and the Indian islands for all ardent spirits. Arrack is often distilled
from a fermented mixture of rice, molasses, and palm wine of the
cocoanut tree or the date palm, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arragonite</ent>⟦br⟧
